('Cobray', 'M11/Nine', '9mm Luger', 'Pistol', 'Semi-Auto', 32, 1982, true, 'United States', 'Semi-automatic MAC-11-pattern pistol in 9mm from SWD/Cobray. The civilian semi-auto successor to the MAC-11. Open-bolt design (early), later changed to closed-bolt to comply with BATF rulings.', 199, 53.0, 9.5, false, false, ARRAY['M11 in .380 ACP', 'PM11'], 'Discontinued', 'Cobray M11', ARRAY['9mm Luger', '.380 ACP'], ARRAY['m11/nine', 'cobray m11', 'm11 nine'], 'Cold War', 'Single-Action', ARRAY['collector'], NULL, 'United States', false, NULL),

('Cobray', 'M12', '.380 ACP', 'Pistol', 'Semi-Auto', 16, 1985, true, 'United States', 'Semi-automatic pistol in .380 ACP based on the MAC-12 pattern. Smaller and lighter than the M11.', 179, 42.0, 8.1, false, false, NULL, 'Discontinued', 'Cobray M12', ARRAY['.380 ACP'], ARRAY['m12', 'cobray m12'], 'Cold War', 'Single-Action', ARRAY['collector'], NULL, 'United States', false, NULL),

('Cobray', 'Terminator', '12 Gauge', 'Shotgun', 'Single-Action', 1, 1986, true, 'United States', 'Single-shot 12-gauge shotgun constructed from a large-diameter steel tube with a simple striker mechanism. Arguably the most primitive firearm ever mass-produced in the United States. Retailed for approximately $70 new.', 70, 64.0, 18.0, false, false, NULL, 'Discontinued', 'Cobray Terminator', ARRAY['12 Gauge'], ARRAY['terminator', 'cobray terminator shotgun'], 'Cold War', 'Single-Action', ARRAY['collector'], 'The Cobray Terminator was cited by Senator Dennis DeConcini on the floor of the Senate as an example of the dangerous cheapness of available firearms. A single-shot 12-gauge made of pipe retailing for $70 became a symbol of the "Saturday Night Special" legislative debate.', 'United States', true, 'Functional Cobray Terminators in any condition have genuine collector curiosity value due to their notoriety and crude construction.'),

