('Detonics', 'CombatMaster', '.45 ACP', 'Pistol', 'Single-Action', 6, 1976, true, 'United States', 'Ultra-compact 1911 in .45 ACP with a 3.5" barrel. One of the first commercially successful compact 1911s, predating most American manufacturers'' compact offerings by years. Produced in both Seattle and later revived versions.', 799, 28.0, 6.75, false, false, ARRAY['CombatMaster Mark V', 'CombatMaster in 9mm'], 'Discontinued', 'Detonics CombatMaster', ARRAY['.45 ACP', '9mm Luger', '.38 Super'], ARRAY['combatmaster', 'detonics 45'], 'Modern', 'Single-Action', ARRAY['carry', 'collector'], 'The Detonics CombatMaster was one of the first to demonstrate that a .45 ACP 1911 could be shortened to truly concealable dimensions without sacrificing function — a concept that Kimber, Springfield, and others later popularized.', 'United States', true, 'Original Seattle-production Detonics command collector premiums over later Indiana and Texas revival productions.'),

