-- ── DWM ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────
('DWM (Deutsche Waffen- und Munitionsfabriken)', 'Luger P08', '9mm Parabellum', 'Pistol', 'Single-Action', 8, 1900, true, 'Germany', 'The Luger P08 — designed by Georg Luger and manufactured by DWM from 1900. The toggle-lock semi-automatic pistol that became one of the most iconic firearms of the 20th century. Standard German military sidearm in WWI and WWII. DWM-manufactured examples from the pre-WWI and WWI era are among the most collectible military pistols.', NULL, 30.0, 8.75, true, true, ARRAY['Artillery Luger (8" barrel)', 'Navy Luger (6" barrel)', 'DWM Commercial'], 'Discontinued', 'Luger P08', ARRAY['9mm Parabellum', '7.65mm Parabellum'], ARRAY['luger', 'p08', 'dwm luger', 'pistole 08'], 'World War I', 'Single-Action', ARRAY['military', 'collector'], 'DWM also developed and manufactured the 9mm Parabellum cartridge specifically for the Luger pistol — the cartridge that became the most widely used pistol cartridge in history.', 'Germany', true, 'DWM-manufactured P08s from the 1900-1918 period command significant premiums. Artillery (Artillerieluger) variants with matching detachable stocks are extremely valuable. Chamber stamps, date codes, and proof marks are critical to valuation.'),

('DWM (Deutsche Waffen- und Munitionsfabriken)', 'Luger P08 Artillery', '9mm Parabellum', 'Pistol', 'Single-Action', 32, 1914, true, 'Germany', 'Long-barreled (8") Luger with a 32-round snail drum magazine, designed for German artillery and storm troops in WWI. The drum magazine was a revolutionary high-capacity design for its era.', NULL, 36.0, 13.5, true, false, ARRAY['With TM 08 snail drum', 'With 32-round drum'], 'Discontinued', 'Luger P08', ARRAY['9mm Parabellum'], ARRAY['artillerieluger', 'lange pistole 08', 'lp08', 'artillery luger'], 'World War I', 'Single-Action', ARRAY['military', 'collector'], 'The Artillery Luger with its snail drum magazine was one of the first high-capacity semi-automatic pistols ever issued to military forces. Matching examples with original drum, holster, and loading tools are among the most valuable WWI pistols.', 'Germany', true, 'Matching Artillery Lugers with original 32-round drum, buttstock holster, and loading tool are exceptional collector pieces worth $5,000-$30,000+ depending on condition and markings.'),

('DWM (Deutsche Waffen- und Munitionsfabriken)', 'Mauser C96 (manufactured)', '7.63x25mm Mauser', 'Pistol', 'Single-Action', 10, 1896, true, 'Germany', 'While DWM is most associated with the Luger, the company also manufactured C96 Broomhandle Mauser pistols under license at various periods. DWM was one of the primary ammunition manufacturers and supplied brass to virtually every major caliber of the era.', NULL, 44.0, 11.75, true, false, NULL, 'Discontinued', 'C96 Broomhandle', ARRAY['7.63x25mm Mauser', '9mm Parabellum'], ARRAY['c96', 'broomhandle', 'bolo mauser'], 'Pre-WWI / Old West', 'Single-Action', ARRAY['military', 'collector'], NULL, 'Germany', true, NULL),

